commit.message:
Make tab-width and indent-line-function buffer-local

When we set this globally, we intrude on packages which doesn't
explicitly set these variables. I observed this with mutt-mode.

commit.message: Don't assume any line with a variable isn't an anchor

Rename *-last-selector-line to *-last-anchor-line

We want to indent on directives and blocks, as well
Add setting to never indent blank lines

Fix indentation for functions with >1 argument

This should now be indented properly:

.foo
  color: transparentize(#000000, 0.5)
  left: 0
Lines with variables in them aren't selectors

Further improve indentation

From

a:visited
text-decoration: underline

to

a:visited
  text-decoration: underline

Improve indentation accuracy

- Multiline union selectors are now indented properly

p,
  a

becomes

p,
a

- Certain directives are now indented properly

@include foo
  color: red

becomes

@include foo
color: red

- Single-line comments are now indented properly

// Hello world
  color: red

becomes

// Hello world
color: red

Merge pull request #1 from purcell/patch-1

Tidy up temp file handling

Tidy up temp file handling

- Use `interactive` to better handle operation on regions
- Delegate evaluation of buffer to evaluation of region
- Fix unhelpful docstring: this new format also satisfies `checkdoc`
- Use `make-temp-file` to avoid hardcoding `/tmp`
Differentiate mode tag and respect user temp directory
